Yingli Green Energy Holding Co. plans
to reduce its production costs to $1 per watt of capacity by the
second half of 2012 from about $1.2 per watt in the fourth
quarter of last year, Handelsblatt reported.  Yingli will seek to raise the efficiency of its Panda solar
cells to 20 percent in 2012 from an average 18.5 percent last
year, the newspaper said, citing an interview with Miao Liansheng, the Chinese companyâ€™s chief executive officer.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
